attributes.background:
We further urge the Prime Minister to personally:

	Condemn the on-going military escalation and deplore the human suffering caused by such escalation;

	Call upon all warring parties to immediately stop attacks on hospitals, schools and churches and their surroundings and to recognize such sites as safe zones;

	Ensure that the civilian population is respected and protected in all circumstances, in accordance with the principle of distinction between civilian and military targets and thus avoid indiscriminate attacks;

	Call upon all warring parties to immediately end campaigns of sexual atrocities and to fully observe humanitarian laws and internationally agreed human rights;

	Demand that President Paul Kagame; and President Yoweri Museveni do immediately cease all forms of support to Laurent Nkunda

	Insist that health professionals, human rights defenders and Aid workers and their supplies are given unhindered access to all war affected areas;  and

	Make it clear that, in the event that the above demands are not met, the UK will impose targeted diplomatic, economic and political measures against all those implicated in this conflict.
